<Category category="Winding Temperature Indicators" slug="transformer-winding-temperature-indicators" title="Transformer Winding Temperature Indicator Manufacturer | INNO" description="Compare BWR and BWR2 transformer winding temperature indicators (WTI) for thermal simulation, cooling, alarm, trip and remote output. Get model data." heading="Transformer Winding Temperature Indicators (WTI)" eyebrow="BWR and BWR2 manufacturer and supplier" intro="Select a WTI for traditional simulated transformer winding temperature indication, cooling-stage control, alarm, trip and compatible remote output." definition="A transformer winding temperature indicator, or WTI, combines measured top-oil temperature with a calibrated load-current heating effect. BWR and BWR2 models indicate simulated winding temperature and provide contacts for transformer cooling and protection logic." selectionTitle="How to Select a Transformer Winding Temperature Indicator" selectionText="Define the simulated winding temperature scale, CT secondary input and heating configuration first. Then specify cooling, alarm and trip contacts, Pt100 or 4-20 mA output, compound transmitter, capillary, mounting and replacement interfaces." />
